{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9e494375-d3ea-4250-9d81-5954ec2e662c","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, make two changes:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the VSTest property:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it — `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0` uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default**. The `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was opting you *out* of it. Removing it switches you to the new platform.\n\n**What changes at runtime:**\n- Tests run via the new `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` runner instead of `vstest.console`.\n- `dotnet test` still works, but under the hood it launches the new test host.\n- CLI output format is slightly different.\n\n**Things to verify after the switch:**\n- Run `dotnet test` and confirm all tests pass.\n- If you use `.runsettings`, they're still supported but some custom adapters may need updates.\n- If you rely on `vstest`-specific command-line flags (e.g., `--logger`), check the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform CLI docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview) for equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"980d2793-ef0c-4f09-9769-e68e54d1328d","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"1BD4:BB4CA:20EDEF3:24518B1:6A03CEC1"},"id":"dd6a90d3-6a81-4603-952f-f267400f48ab","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:07:24.426Z","parentId":"134797d0-9f70-425f-9743-13cd6f175804"}
